The Osun State Resident Electoral Commissioner (REC), Prof. Abdulganiy Raji revealed on Tuesday that non-sensitive materials have already been batched to the Polling Unit Level and are ready to be conveyed to the Registration Area Centres (RACs) for the conduct of the state governorship election. He said this during an election stakeholders’ meeting held in Osogbo for the Osun gubernatorial poll coming on Saturday. Prof Raji continued that sensitive materials would arrive in Osun state on Tuesday. “Production of Maps of all Polling Units in the state both electronically and hardcopy for ease of movement and location of Polling Units by the Staff of INEC, and trained officials are ready to deploy. “INEC had met with stakeholders in their categories while this particular meeting is the final one towards the July 16 election, the conduct of mock accreditation in selected LGAs to ensure the functionality of BVAS and readiness assessment of the election process. “As I speak to you, all non-sensitive materials are already batched to Polling Unit Level and ready to be conveyed to the RACs, sensitive materials should arrive today, production of maps of all polling units in the state both electronically and hardcopy for ease of movement and location of polling units by the staff of INEC, poll officials are trained and ready for deployment, security personnel in the state has been trained,” he said.